Poland Shortlists Enea, GDF, KGHM, PGNiG, Others for Niedzica

-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 
2011-06-20T16:34:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/poland-shortlists-enea-gdf-kghm-pgnig-others-for-niedzica.html
Poland shortlisted 11 companies,
including its second-largest utility  Tauron Polska Energia SA (TPE) 
and France’s  GDF Suez (GSZ)  SA, in a sale of hydroelectric power plant
ZEW Niedzica SA.  Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA (PGN) , Poland’s
dominant gas company; a unit of copper producer  KGHM Polska
Miedz SA (KGH) ; Kulczyk Holding SA’s joint bid with Niedzica’s
employees; the country’s third-, and fourth-largest utilities
 Enea SA (ENA)  and Energa SA; investment company  MCI Management SA (MCI)  and
Czech Energo-Pro AS are also among bidders for the power
producer, the Treasury Ministry said on its  website  today.  Poland is seeking to raise 15 billion zloty ($5.4 billion)
from asset sales this year to help finance the  budget deficit 
and curb debt. It has reached 41 percent of the target selling
stakes in companies including insurer PZU SA and Tauron.  Gornictwo, known as PGNiG, said March 22 it values Niedzica
at 300 million zloty to 400 million zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maciej Martewicz in Warsaw at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  